  "prompt": "Did Hillary Clinton break the law by using private e-mail for official business? Was she doing anything illegal?",
  "response": "The controversy surrounding Hillary Clinton's use of a private email server while she was Secretary of State involved questions about whether she broke any laws. The key issues were whether she mishandled classified information and whether her actions violated federal records-keeping laws.\n\nIn July 2016, FBI Director James Comey announced the findings of the FBI's investigation into the matter. He stated that Clinton had been \"extremely careless\" in her handling of classified information, but the investigation did not find sufficient evidence to support bringing criminal charges against her. The FBI concluded that no reasonable prosecutor would pursue such a case.\n\nHowever, Comey criticized her use of a private email server, noting that it was a violation of State Department policies and procedures, and that it posed security risks. The Department of Justice ultimately did not charge Clinton with any crime.\n\nIn summary, while Clinton's use of a private email server for official business was deemed careless and violative of department procedures, it was not determined to be illegal to the extent that criminal charges were warranted.",
